4. Protocol Architecture

4.1 Soulbound NFT Collection on Stargaze

Our NFT collection is at the core of the protocol, establishing immutable digital identities and governance roles. All NFTs are non-transferable, ensuring that each token remains permanently linked to its original owner.
	‚Ä¢	Truth ID NFT:
	‚Ä¢	Purpose: Acts as a unique, non-transferable identifier for each member.
	‚Ä¢	Role: Grants access to governance functions and the exclusive right to invite new members.
	‚Ä¢	Creator NFT:
	‚Ä¢	Purpose: Awarded to members with significant, one-time contributions.
	‚Ä¢	Mechanism: Initially holds 51% of the voting power; can later be split through co‚Äëcreation negotiations.
	‚Ä¢	Collaborator NFT:
	‚Ä¢	Purpose: Minted daily to recognize individual contributions.
	‚Ä¢	Mechanism: Each token carries a weight from 1 to 7, reflecting the quality and impact of the contribution.
	‚Ä¢	Red Pill NFT:
	‚Ä¢	Purpose: Functions as a weekly voting multiplier.
	‚Ä¢	Mechanism: Minted every Sunday, its multiplier is calculated using the formula:
\text{Multiplier} = (\% \text{Participation} \times \% \text{Alignment} \times 7)
	‚Ä¢	Constraint: A wallet can hold a maximum of 3 Red Pill NFTs; the oldest is burned every 28 days.

4.2 Governance Workflow and Consensus Mechanism

The protocol‚Äôs governance is structured around a daily cycle that uses off‚Äëchain tools (Discord) for initial implementation, with plans to transition on‚Äëchain:
	‚Ä¢	Proposal Submission:
Only members with Truth ID NFTs can submit proposals on designated channels.
	‚Ä¢	Discussion and Voting:
Proposals are discussed and then voted on using a weighted emoji system (detailed below).
	‚Ä¢	Consensus Requirement: Proposals must reach a specific voting threshold (70‚Äì85% alignment) before advancing.

4.3 Off‚ÄëChain Governance on Discord

Currently, the governance process is conducted on Discord, offering a flexible, user-friendly environment:
	‚Ä¢	Channels and Roles:
